<HEADLINE>
OVER 1,900 CONVICTED OF GRAFT IN 7 YEARS: MOJ
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  Jan. 20 (CNA) 01/20/07  14:53:34 (By Y.F. Low)
</P>
<P>
A total of 9,136 people have been indicted in more than 3,500
graft cases under the Ministry of Justice's (MOJ) anti-corruption
operations over the past seven years, 1,916 of whom have been
convicted, with illicit gains seized amounting to more than
NT$28.61 billion (US$872.26 million)), according to tallies
released Saturday by the ministry.
</P>
<P>
Between July 2000 and December 2006, 117 people were indicted in
46 graft cases on average per month, MOJ officials said.
</P>
<P>
In December 2006 alone, 181 people were charged in 55 cases, the
officials said.
</P>
<P>
Of the 9,136 people indicted, 491 were senior-level civil
servants,  577  were people's  representatives,  1,647  were
intermediate-level civil servants, 2,780 were junior-level civil
servants, and 3,641 were ordinary people, they said.
</P>
